# Agent brain

This repo uses the portable `.agent/` brain. Read in order:

1. `.agent/AGENTS.md` — the map.
2. `.agent/memory/personal/PREFERENCES.md`
3. `.agent/memory/semantic/LESSONS.md`
4. `.agent/skills/_index.md` — skills load on demand.
5. `.agent/protocols/permissions.md` — check before tool calls.

## Task framing

See `program.md` for the meta-agent directive.

- Never edit below the `FIXED ADAPTER BOUNDARY` in `agent.py` or `agent-claude.py`.
- Never change `MODEL` from `gpt-5` unless the human explicitly lifts the pin.
- The first run on any branch is always the unmodified baseline.
- Every benchmark iteration runs in a fresh-context subagent — see
  `.agent/skills/subagent-dispatcher/SKILL.md`.
- Both `agent.py` (OpenAI SDK) and `agent-claude.py` (Claude SDK) share this
  brain; keep knowledge SDK-agnostic in skills + memory.
